1.3 ggplot function

  • First argument: data frame
  • Second argument: aes()
ggplot(diamonds, aes())

2 With x in aes() in ggplot()

2.1 geom_hist(): histogram

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.2 + facet_wrap()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~color)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~cut)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.3 scales option in facet_wrap()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~cut, scales = "free_y")
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.4 + facet_grid()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(cut~color)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.5 scales option in facet_grid()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(cut~color, scales = "free_y")
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

2.6 geom_density() + facet_wrap()

You can try!

3 With x and y in aes() in ggplot()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price))

3.1 geom_point: Scatter plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point(size = 0.5)

3.2 + facet_wrap()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point(size = 0.5) + 
  facet_wrap(~cut)

3.3 geom_point() + geom_smooth + facet_wrap()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=table, y=price)) + 
  geom_point(size = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth() +
  facet_wrap(~cut)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

3.4 geom_boxplot(): box plot

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=clarity, y=price)) + 
  geom_boxplot()

3.5 + facet_wrap()

ggplot(diamonds, aes(x=clarity, y=price)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  facet_wrap(~color)
